<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-14-0865 </DOCNO><TEXT>Pb(TiZr)O/sub 3/ solid solutions with a small Ti content (up to 10%) havebeen investigated to study the possibilities of controlling ferroelectric-antiferroelectricphase boundaries by means of a constant electric field under high pressures.''Composition-temperature'' and p-T phase diagrams have been constructedon the basis of the permittivity temperature dependence of solid solutions.Dependence of permittivity on the external constant magnetic field hasbeen investigated under 6 kbar pressure and 20, 35, 50, 65, 80 and 95deg C. Considerable hysteresis of the phase boundary has been observedboth by temperature and pressure.</TEXT></DOC>